Yona Ellis, marketing manager of the Barefoot Wine Beach Rescue Project, said, 'We're shocked and amazed with the findings and can't wait to see what our volunteers continue to find at our remaining beach cleans.

'Little did we know that eight years ago the British beaches were littered with treasure - it's fascinating!

Hugo Tagholm, Surfers Against Sewage Chief Executive, collaborates with Barefoot Wine tackle marine litter by encouraging local communities to keep their beaches barefoot friendly.

He said: 'Unfortunately marine litter causes long-term problems for our beaches, and the very special wildlife that lives in our oceans which is why projects such as this are so important.'

